product_name: MACStudio Fix Every-Wear All-Over Face Concealer Pen
summary: SummaryMAC's Studio Fix Every-Wear All-Over Face Pen is a multi-use concealer pen with medium-to-full buildable coverage and a natural matte finish that is transfer-proof, waterproof and wears for 36 hours. This multi-use concealer formula applies, builds and blends easily.
details: DetailsBenefitsMulti-use, lightweight, hydrating concealer formula36HR longwearMedium-to-full buildable coverage & natural matte finishDoesn't settle, cake, crease or streakTransfer- & waterproof, sweat- & humidity-resistantDermatologist testedDoes not cause acneSuitable for all skin typesFeaturesClick, tap, go!Conceal and correct with our multi-use concealer pen that doesn't cake or creaseUse to spot conceal blemishes & undereye circles or use all over to correct redness and even skin tonePortable concealer is perfect for on-the-go touchupsKey IngredientsInfused with Vitamin E, Hyaluronic Acid and CaffeineItem 2611018How To UseTwist the bottom of the concealer pen to unlock and click half-way to spot-conceal or all the way for all-over coverage. Using MAC's 171 Smooth Edge All-Over Face Brush or your fingertips, blend the product into skin. Twist the bottom again to lock and snap the lid onto the pen.IngredientsWater\\Aqua\\Eau, Dimethicone, Methyl Trimethicone, Trimethylsiloxysilicate/Dimethiconol Crosspolymer, Butylene Glycol, Neopentyl Glycol Diheptanoate, Phenyl Trimethicone, Polymethyl Methacrylate, Ppg-12/Smdi Copolymer, Lauryl Peg-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Tocopheryl Acetate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Lecithin, Caffeine, Triethyl Citrate, Methicone, Peg-10 Dimethicone, Laureth-7, Alumina, Silica, Magnesium Aluminum Silicate, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Polysilicone-11, Xanthan Gum, Sodium Chloride, Dimethicone Silylate, Dimethicone/Peg-10/15 Crosspolymer, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Caprylyl Glycol, Hexylene Glycol, Dipropylene Glycol, Zinc Stearate, Disodium Edta, Bht, Phenoxyethanol, Sodium Citrate, Potassium Sorbate, Sodium Dehydroacetate, \[+/- Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499)\] \Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Twist the bottom of the concealer pen to unlock and click half-way to spot-conceal or all the way for all-over coverage. Using MAC's 171 Smooth Edge All-Over Face Brush or your fingertips, blend the product into skin. Twist the bottom again to lock and snap the lid onto the pen.

reviews.headline: It can be decent , but can be bad
reviews.comments: I haven't worn MAC in years because of them not being cruelty free. Call it weird, but there is no reason why they need to test on animals. I ended up wearing Mac at a wedding that I was in and couldn't believe its staying power. So I bought this. It's what they used. Anyway , I live in the desert and it actually does ok there. Stays on pretty good most days , but when I travel to the coast , it's horrid. I don't know if it's the humidity or salt , but it  goes on badly and doesn't stay on. I have under eye circles and malasma. I also find it doesn't go on great at all as a foundation. I won't buy it again. It had its moments , but it's not great.

reviews.headline: Don't buy !!!!!
reviews.comments: this is the worst product I have ever purchased. the pump is clogged and nothing is coming out and I have 3/4 of the concealer still left in there. Total rip off.

reviews.headline: Absolutely in Love!
reviews.comments:
The best yet. I'm 51 years young, I've been wearing MAC for the last 10 years! 
This is by far the best!

reviews.headline: Never
reviews.comments: Product pump does not release makeup. Need to pump multiple times. Had 3, liked the first one bought again.2nd time it fell and didn't work, pump didn't pump. 3rd time still having trouble with pump. Can NOT get what's left of makeup out of tube container. Get the bottle better.

reviews.headline: I would not buy this product again
reviews.comments: This product was suggested since the one I use regularly was not in stock. I do not like the way it look and it has a dry finish. It is the same color NW45 as the other that I wear but it looks darker with no red tone to it. I would not buy this again.

reviews.headline: Yes love the feel and coverage
reviews.comments: I got this product on a recommedation from a friend and it was spot on!!

reviews.headline: Definitely No
reviews.comments: This MAC foundation makes my face look like the texture of an orange peel.... It is streaky & cakey looking (I have tried different things and nothing helped).... The packaging looks cool and albeit the button gets pushed while in makeup bag and waste product. if they made the cap with an insert that goes into spout that would help prevent it from leaking and wasting product.

reviews.headline: Great for Nights out!
reviews.comments: So, this is the old Prolongwear Nourishing Waterproof Foundation. I dont love how little product you get but I will say, the product formula still slaps. I reserve this strictly for nights out/ events. Full coverage, longwear, satiny finish, photographs beautifully and the container is SUPER travel friendly. I really hate that they call it a "concealer". Can you use it that way? Maybe, if you're concealing underneath your foundation but I'd still say it's better used as a true foundation. Also, VERY IMPORTANT, because it's waterproof brush application is BEST! If you use a beauty blender/sponge you MUST use it dry. The water in a sponge can make the formula behave weird.

reviews.headline: Just ok
reviews.comments: I got this because I was looking for the MAC Pro long wear concealer and Ulta no longer carries it in store. The girl that works there said essentially its the same exact formula but for the full face. Does ok on the whole face with exception to the under eye and the color did oxidized and turned orangeish. I wouldn't purchase again.

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: I use this as a foundation. It works well for light coverage, or building for a full coverage look. A little really does go a long way.

reviews.headline: Makeup makeup
reviews.comments: I think I was expecting this to be more natural but it's pretty cakey and not great for layering so using as a concealer wasn't the best. Using it as a foundation was okay if you want really full coverage but it's definitely for those days you MAKEUP

reviews.headline: I would buy this again. Great product
reviews.comments: This is the only makeup I use.

reviews.headline: I would not but this again for myself
reviews.comments: I'm sure this is a great product to start using in your 20's or 30's. But I don't think it's the best for much Older people

reviews.headline: finally for oily skin
reviews.comments: I wasn't aware of this foundation until a makeup specialist helped me. she saw how my clinique foundation was sliding off especially wearing glasses. since wearing this mac foundation, I received numerous compliments. my bestie said it looks more natural & blends in rather than cakey looking. even when I'm in humidity or it's hot, the foundation looks great!! she recommended the charlotte tilbury spray so both have been a great combo ðŸ˜ƒ I use a dense brush for this foundation.

reviews.headline: New Favorite
reviews.comments: I was a devotee of the Pro Long wear Nourishing Waterproof Foundation and I was alarmed when it was discontinued. This is my new staple, lasts all day and night and still looks great after 12 to 14 hour days. I use it as a 2in 1 foundation and concealer.

reviews.headline: Shades are a bit off
reviews.comments: The shade range runs light I usually get nc 30 in summer and for this one I am nc38. I use it all over just 2 to 3 clicks is what I like and the coverage is pretty full I loved it ! I don't get oily through the day I set with a loose powder.

reviews.headline: Truly not impressed for mac sadlyâ€¦
reviews.comments: I do love when I put it alll over how it ends up looking. It smears quite a bit tho, and I dont feel like it stays put as much as it should. If I so much as touch it it disipates, even though I bought the mac spray all night. My milani was less cakey than this. I was taught awhile ago to start using maybe a little bit more of foundation so it really gives that all over coverage. I keep reading people saying a little goes a long way but I don't feel this is the case for this or the other mac foundation I bought. I like the other mac one better I bought both at the same time thinking this pen was a concealer happy I did buy it. At the same time I likely will likely purchase the other mac foundation I have when I run out I feel its a little less chalky.

reviews.headline: Mac Studio Fix
reviews.comments: Love the fact that it's waterproof. Colors are just a little bit hard to match. Hides hyperpigmentation fairly well. I do have to apply several coats for it to completely hide it. It does give me all day coverage. Most of the night coverage. I will definitely purchase this product again.

reviews.headline: Great as an Undereye concealer
reviews.comments: I only use this as an Undereye concealer and i love it. It is very creamy and gives a lot of coverage. Sits great under powder foundation. The pen is a little tricky to use-i have to be very careful to not dispense too much. I kept the little stopper pin for the applicator tip so i think it will stay fresh and not ooze out.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I was gifted the Mac Studio FX by Bzzagent in exchange for a review. I was pleasantly surprised by the Mac Studio Fix concealer. I have very dark eye bags. My bags are almost a dark gray shade and take a bit of work to cover up. I've tried a handful of concealers both drugstore and higher-end makeup brands, and it usually takes two or three dabs of concealer to fully cover my eyebags. Even then sometimes I will still have some gray peak through the concealer. When I tried the FX, the gray seemed to disappear after one dab, and the color was very opaque. I didn't notice any gray peeking out. I loved the blendability. I used my finger the blend the FX, and I noticed how it naturally blended into the skin. I usually have to fidget with my foundation to hide the seams of the concealer. But with the FX, I could directly blend the concealer, without adding anything else. As a bonus, I found that the scent isn't too fragrant, and is very light, compared to other concealers. 
  
Design: The pen uses a twist mechanic to lock the concealer, when not in use. This is a great feature and addresses the inevitable spillage that may happen in a full purse. I really liked this design feature, especially because the pen was so big. The pen is also able to stand up by itself, and could easily be stored with liquid foundation bottles.  My family members struggled with the twist knob, assuming that you had to push the button on the bottom. But I found the pen pretty intuitive, with the twist knob and the press button mechanic. 

Pros:
I love the applicator. One of my grips with liquid products is the unsanitary nature of a lot of foundation/concealer. Foundation/concealer applicators tend to touch the skin, which degrades the product faster. 
Cons: the applicator dishes out pea-sized drops which is often recommended by makeup gurus/and artists to distribute the product evenly on the face, but I wish I was able to control the amount.
faceoff_positive.headline: Large Concealer with a Cool Lock Mechanic

So I received this as a free product first of all but I definitely still preferred the pro longwear foundation to this pen the pen is pretty solid and bulky and I havent gotten to the end of it yet but I suspect it wont be as easy to squeeze out the remaining product until I can refill as the foundation was. Also worth mentioning the foundation was 
Point 84fl 25ml for around 40 while the pen that tells you half a click is all it needs its not possible to do a half click the pen has only point 41fl 12ml it does not say or claim to be a concealer and I didnt need it to be a concealer I needed it to be the foundation product i was using years before they discontinued it and guess what IT KIND OF IS lol just half the product at BASICALLY same price and I really already see getting any last drops out a huge problem because now it is caged in a hard shell plastic container that is even bigger than the old foundation bottle the product is a little different than the old one and you prob dont wear the same shade it does not seem as matte as the last one so you will prob need a powder although it does not say it is concealer nor will you ever be able to get out half a click of product EVER Im sure this will be great for my self esteem I needed a full coverage foundation now ill be going through it like crazy and I guess my giant man hands will never be able to get out half a click because im sure nobody would put out a product that was impossible to half click people regularly go around half way clicking things try it with your pen if of course you dont destroy it with your big man hands pushing it. So I will say this product exists, you will need at least 2 if you expect it to last as long as your foundation which I sincerely hope you are able to afford I am not looking forward to the trial and error finding a new product to replace it with considering spending more on a higher end product since it would still be cheaper than 2 of these to last the length they previously did if you have never used this product in its foundation form then maybe it will be cool but it is BULKY Ill post pics.
